      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis model credibility supported by published literature survey",
      "description": "A structured review of 34 peer-reviewed publications on CFD-based hemolysis prediction in rotary blood pumps was conducted. The review confirmed that the power-law hemolysis model employed in this analysis has been widely applied to centrifugal pump geometries under comparable flow conditions, and that reported RH predictions generally fall within 10–20% of reported bench measurements across the surveyed studies. The assessment team concludes that the body of literature provides sufficient indirect support for the model's predictive capability under CPB operating conditions.",
